Charity by private individuals up 6-fold in five years

Private philanthropy is on a steady rise in the country and this is expected to increase in the future, thanks to higher GDP growth and an increase in number of ultra-high net-worth individuals (UHNWI) in the country. In fact, funding from individual philanthropists is even outpacing contributions from foreign sources and corporate social responsibility (CSR) efforts, according to a recent report by Bain & Company. Find out moreâ€¦ 
